[h1]Loops[/h1]

[b][/b]A [b]loop [/b]repeatedly executes a set of statements until a particular condition is satisfied. 

A [b]while [/b]loop statement repeatedly executes a target statement as long as a given condition remains [b]true[/b].
[b]Syntax:[/b] [code format="cpp"][b]while [/b](condition) {
   statement(s);
}[/code]
The loop iterates while the condition is [b]true[/b].
[note]At the point when the condition becomes [b]false[/b], program control is shifted to the line that immediately follows the loop.[/note]

quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to print x's value to the screen 5 times.
[!raw!]
int x = 1;
{0} (x <= 5) {
 cout << "value is " << x << endl;
 x = {1} + 1;
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The while Loop[/h1]

The loop's [b]body [/b]is the block of statements within curly braces.
[b]For example:[/b] [code format="cpp" codeId="200"]int num = 1;
while (num < 6) {
  cout << "Number: " << num << endl;
  num = num + 1;
}

/* Outputs
Number: 1
Number: 2
Number: 3
Number: 4
Number: 5 
*/[/code]
The example above declares a variable equal to 1 (int num = 1).
The [b]while [/b]loop checks the condition (num < 6), and executes the statements in its body, which increment the value of [b]num [/b]by one each time the loop runs. 
[note]After the 5th iteration, [b]num [/b]becomes 6, and the condition is evaluated to [b]false[/b], and the loop stops running.[/note]

quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to increment bacon's value by 2 and print only the even values.
[!raw!]
int bacon = 0;
{0} (bacon <= 20) {
 cout << "bacon is " << bacon << endl;
 bacon = bacon + {1};
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The while Loop [/h1]

The increment value can be changed. If changed, the number of times the loop is run will change, as well.[code format="cpp" codeId="201"]int num = 1;
while (num < 6) {
  cout << "Number: " << num << endl;
  [b]num = num + 3;[/b]
}

/* Outputs
Number: 1
Number: 4 
*/[/code] 
[note]Without a statement that eventually evaluates the loop condition to [b]false[/b], the loop will continue indefinitely.[/note]
